elements.title: Maria Moscisca (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that when Lviv-born Maria Moscisca (pictured) performed the title role of Verdi's La traviata at the San Francisco Opera in 1913, a review described her as "the impersonation of grace and refinement"?

elements.title: Zungwini Mountain skirmishes (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Evelyn Wood called off the Zungwini Mountain skirmishes after learning of the Zulu victory over the British at the Battle of Isandlwana?

elements.title: Metropolitan main line (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Metropolitan main line was the first electrified revenue rapid transit in the United States?

elements.title: Baucau Airport (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the only ever hijacking of a Royal Australian Air Force aircraft began at Baucau Airport, East Timor, in 1975?

elements.title: Joseph Mleziva (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Wisconsin farmer-lawmaker Joseph Mleziva refused to run for a fifth term in 1948, saying, "I can't afford to continue and, besides, I'm tired of taking the abuse that comes with the job"?

elements.title: Monumento a los Constructores (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that those who toppled the Monumento a los Constructores said that it was "a symbol of subordination, representation of slavery and an emblem of the Spanish genocide"?

elements.title: KSMN (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Red Blanchard, the owner of Iowa radio station KSMN, commuted 800 miles (1280 km) by plane from Mason City each week to host a radio show in Chicago?

elements.title: the cricket (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that one of Josquin des Prez's most popular works is about the cricket?
